---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = "February 20, 2026";
---

<Base title="Name It! Privacy Policy — Flatiron Kids" description="Privacy policy for Name It!">
  <section class="pt-36 pb-20 px-6">
    <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto prose prose-invert prose-headings:font-semibold prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-brand-400 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline">
      <h1>Name It! — Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm !mt-2">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        Name It! collects limited telemetry data to improve our voice recognition. We do not
        collect personal information, and we do not require accounts.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Collect</h2>
      <p>To improve voice recognition accuracy, we may collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Anonymous voice recognition performance metrics (e.g. success/failure rates)</li>
        <li>Device type and OS version</li>
        <li>App version</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is not tied to any individual and cannot be used to identify your child.
        We do not record or transmit audio.
      </p>

      <h2>No Advertising</h2>
      <p>Name It! does not contain advertisements of any kind.</p>

      <h2>No Third-Party Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell, trade, or share any data with third parties.</p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Name It! is designed for children. We collect no personal information and comply
        with COPPA and all applicable children's privacy regulations.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes, we will update this page with a new date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions? Reach us at <a href="mailto:support@flatironkids.co">support@flatironkids.co</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Base>
